The Gombe State Government has on Friday relaxed the 12-hour curfew it imposed on Gombe metropolis in response to the crisis experienced in some parts of the city since last Saturday. In a statement, the Acting Secretary of the State Government, Mr James Pisagih, said Governor Ibrahim Hassan Dankwambo had directed that the curfew be relaxed to 12:00 midnight. “Reports received by Governor Dankwambo from security agencies indicated that relative peace has been recorded in most parts of Gombe metropolis that were hitherto under dusk to dawn curfew. Accordingly, he has directed for the review of the curfew in Gombe from 12:00 midnight to 6:00am daily,” he said. Mr Pisagih however said in some part of the metropolis the curfew still remains from 6pm to 6am, “normalcy has not been completely achieved in some parts of the bypass areas of Bagadaza and Nayi Nawa, therefore the curfew in the areas still remain from 6pm to 6am daily. BREAKING: Gombe government reviews curfew on Gombe metropolis Govt reviews Gombe metropolis curfew Government relaxes Gombe metro curfew to 10pm Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin